description.value: Album half-bound (re-bound) in brown leather, with a heavily banded spine and a binder's label (J Howe, London), containing 129 leaves with 263 drawings (including 4 by pupils Jones, George Lance, Tom Lascar and Edward Chatfield) mounted by the artist (on the recto, verso or both sides), academical studies and studies for pictures, some figures based on the Elgin Marbles, others with the artist or other people as models; also one blank leaf and marbled fixed and free endpapers; including studies, mainly limbs, hands and feet, for "Christ's Entry into Jerusalem", 'Pharaoh', 'Dentatus', 'Judgement of Solomon', 'Macbeth', 'Lazarus', 'Romeo', Joseph and Mary resting on the road to Egypt', 'Penitent Girl', 'Agony in the Garden', 'Silenus', 'Puck', and anatomical sketches. 1805-42 Most sketches in black chalk, some with red chalk or graphite, several heightened with white; others in graphite or pen and ink; one in watercolour and another in red chalk
